New tools for car expertise
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars who have suffered damage are brought back to a garage, where an expert has to assess the damage suffered and the cost of repair.
Each damage is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and working time can be a long and complex work.
Calculating the cost of repair by hand between EUR 20,000 and EUR 30,000, including the coins and the workforce can take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
This is why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Providers of services and solutions for damage assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers, then processing them and offering them to their customers as a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American Solera group, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies in competition in the area of evaluation tools and the development of sector information are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, each of them provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so in the past five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
When a new car comes into the market, these companies start working.
This is a very hard work, because each of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be cataloged and its price recorded.
In addition, a "smart" graphic image of each model can be clicked on the different parts of a car.
If this is a massively sold model, the work can be completed within a week if the process advances very quickly.
If it is a car that is not sold, it can take three or four months. At present, Audatex has full information on 99.2% of the cars marketed in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have information about Porsches, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini.
For vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%.
To carry out the documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centres worldwide (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), each of which is specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than 100 technicians (generally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million each year to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer a variety of products.
The most frequent application is repair and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for the management of crack parts or for the calculation of the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but in the United States.
